<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="418" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,692,716]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin prefix 
<emphasis box="[912,962,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">fort-</emphasis>
(= strong) and the Latin 
<emphasis box="[1242,1325,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">juxtalis</emphasis>
(= juxta), referring to the very strong juxta in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
